
                            Server Creation - Node Js & Express

                                    Basic Commands


1. create package.json - npm init
2. install Express - npm i express 
3. server run : nodemon index.js
4. Instal JWT - npm i jsonwebtoken


                                    Basic steps
1. create a folder for server 
2. create pakage.json
3. install express
4. create index.js
5. import express
6. create server app using express
7. set up port number for server 
8. HTTP request resolving 
9. Run server 
10. responce code
        1xx - information
        2xx - success
        3xx - Redirection
        4xx - client error
        5xx - server error

11. JWT Token - JSON Web Token

        11.1 Token Genaration - sign()
        11.2 Token validation - verify()

12. Middeleware 

        12.1 Application specific Middleware
        12.2 Router specific Middleware

13. Data base Integration - mongoose

        13.1 Import mongoose
        13.2 connect the db using mongoose
        13.3 create model using mongoose

14. Resolve asynchronus - promise

        14.1 resolve state - then()
        14.2 reject state - catch()
        
15. CORS - cross origin resorce sharing